  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Cut the tofu into 1-inch cubes and place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Drizzle the tofu with a little bit of oil and toss to coat.",
    "In a blender or food processor, combine coconut milk, curry paste, soy sauce, honey, rice vinegar, garlic, and ginger. Blend until smooth.",
    "Pour the sauce over the tofu and toss to coat.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper to taste.",
    "Bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the tofu is golden brown and the sauce is bubbly.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped cilantro or scallions if desired."
